<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="141" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="141">
Genus 
<taxonomicName LSID="A6689F66-B1FE-55D1-87E6-DCB4FF82E22A" authority="Meigen, 1824" authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1824" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Sarcophaga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sarcophaga" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Sarcophaga Meigen, 1824</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="141" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="141">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1824" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Sarcophaga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sarcophaga" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Sarcophaga</taxonomicName>
Meigen, 1824: 305. Type species: 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Musca" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Musca carnaria" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carnaria">Musca carnaria</taxonomicName>
Linnaeus, 1758, by subsequent designation of 
<bibRefCitation author="Partington, CF" journalOrPublisher="Japanese Journal of Sanitary Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" refId="B26" refString="Partington, CF, 1837. The British Cyclopaedia of Natural History: Combining a Scientific Classification of Animals, Plants, and Minerals: with a Popular View of their Habits. Economy, and Structure 3(Part 37): 577-640." title="The British Cyclopaedia of Natural History: Combining a Scientific Classification of Animals, Plants, and Minerals: with a Popular View of their Habits. Economy, and Structure 3 (Part 37): 577 - 640." year="1837">Partington (1837</bibRefCitation>
: 607).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="141">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wei" authorityYear="2005" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Magnicauda" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Magnicauda" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Magnicauda</taxonomicName>
Wei, 2005: 405. Type species: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wei" authorityYear="2005" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Magnicauda" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Magnicauda linjiangensis" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="linjiangensis">Magnicauda linjiangensis</taxonomicName>
Wei, 2005, by original designation. Syn. nov.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="141">
<taxonomicName family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Maginicauda" higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Maginicauda" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" rank="genus">Maginicauda</taxonomicName>
: 
<bibRefCitation author="Wei, LM" editor="Jin, DC" journalOrPublisher="Guizhou Science and Technology Publishing House, Guiyang" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" pagination="404 - 409" refId="B40" refString="Wei, LM, 2005. Sarcophagidae. In: Jin, DC, Li, ZZ, Eds., Insects from Xishui Landscape. Guizhou Science and Technology Publishing House, Guiyang: 404 - 409" title="Sarcophagidae." volumeTitle="Insects from Xishui Landscape." year="2005">Wei (2005</bibRefCitation>
: 409). Incorrect original spelling of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wei" authorityYear="2005" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Magnicauda" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Magnicauda" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Magnicauda</taxonomicName>
, by First Reviser action in the present paper.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="141">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lehrer &amp; Wei" authorityYear="2010" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Leigongshanophaga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Leigongshanophaga" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Leigongshanophaga</taxonomicName>
Lehrer &amp; Wei, 2010: 8. Type species: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wei &amp; Yang" authorityYear="2007" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Sarcophaga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sarcophaga catoptosa" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="catoptosa">Sarcophaga catoptosa</taxonomicName>
Wei &amp; Yang, 2007 [= 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pape &amp; Baenziger" authorityYear="2003" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Sarcophaga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sarcophaga suthep" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="suthep">Sarcophaga suthep</taxonomicName>
Pape &amp; 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Bänziger">Baenziger</normalizedToken>
, 2003], by original designation. Syn. nov. For other synonyms, see 
<bibRefCitation author="Pape, T" journalOrPublisher="International" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" pagination="1 - 558" refId="B22" refString="Pape, T, 1996. Catalogue of the Sarcophagidae of the world (Insecta: Diptera). Memoirs on Entomology. International 8: 1 - 558" title="Catalogue of the Sarcophagidae of the world (Insecta: Diptera). Memoirs on Entomology." volume="8" year="1996">Pape (1996)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="141" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="141">
<bibRefCitation author="Verves, YuG" journalOrPublisher="Priamus" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" pagination="1 - 282" refId="B37" refString="Verves, YuG, Khrokalo, LA, 2020. Review of the taxa of Calliphoridae and Sarcophagidae (Diptera) studied by the late Prof. Andy Z. Lehrer. Priamus 44: 1 - 282" title="Review of the taxa of Calliphoridae and Sarcophagidae (Diptera) studied by the late Prof. Andy Z. Lehrer." volume="44" year="2020">Verves and Khrokalo (2020</bibRefCitation>
: 204) proposed 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lehrer &amp; Wei" authorityYear="2010" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Leigongshanophaga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Leigongshanophaga" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Leigongshanophaga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Lehrer &amp; Wei, 2010 as a new synonym of the valid genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rohdendorf" authorityYear="1937" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Rosellea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Rosellea" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Rosellea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Rohdendorf, 1937, but 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/00379271.2011.10697723" author="Xue, W" journalOrPublisher="Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" pagination="303 - 329" refId="B46" refString="Xue, W, Verves, YG, Du, J, 2011. A review of subtribe Boettcheriscina Verves 1990 (Diptera: Sarcophagidae), with descriptions of a new species and genus from China. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France 47 (3-4): 303 - 329, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1080/00379271.2011.10697723" title="A review of subtribe Boettcheriscina Verves 1990 (Diptera: Sarcophagidae), with descriptions of a new species and genus from China." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/00379271.2011.10697723" volume="47" year="2011">Xue et al. (2011</bibRefCitation>
: 320) proposed the same earlier. As argued below, we consider 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wei &amp; Yang" authorityYear="2007" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Sarcophaga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sarcophaga catoptosa" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="catoptosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Sarcophaga catoptosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Wei &amp; Yang, 2007, which is the type species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lehrer &amp; Wei" authorityYear="2010" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Leigongshanophaga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Leigongshanophaga" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Leigongshanophaga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Lehrer &amp; Wei, 2010, to be a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pape &amp; Baenziger" authorityYear="2003" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Sarcophaga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sarcophaga suthep" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="suthep">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Sarcophaga suthep</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Pape &amp; 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Bänziger">Baenziger</normalizedToken>
, 2003, syn. nov., and we follow 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4668.3.6" author="Wang, C" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" pagination="410 - 420" refId="B38" refString="Wang, C, Gao, YY, Pape, T, Zhang, D, 2019. Redefinition of Cornexcisia Fan and Kano, 2000 (Diptera: Sarcophagidae), with the first description of the female of Sarcophaga kurahashii (Shinonaga and Tumrasvin, 1979). Zootaxa 4668 (3): 410 - 420, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4668.3.6" title="Redefinition of Cornexcisia Fan and Kano, 2000 (Diptera: Sarcophagidae), with the first description of the female of Sarcophaga kurahashii (Shinonaga and Tumrasvin, 1979)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4668.3.6" volume="4668" year="2019">Wang et al. (2019)</bibRefCitation>
in treating this species in 
<taxonomicName authority="Cornexcisia" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Sarcophaga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sarcophaga (Cornexcisia) subsp. subgenus" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" species="suthep" subGenus="Cornexcisia" subSpecies="subgenus">Sarcophaga subgenus Cornexcisia</taxonomicName>
Fan &amp; Kano, 2000.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
